    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PUCCH beamforming data handling in UL TTI processing\n\n### Summary\nThe UL TTI request processing in the NR PHY interface was not correctly handling beamforming data for PUCCH PDUs. This caused incorrect packing/unpacking of PUCCH configuration parameters, leading to unexpected behavior when processing uplink control channel requests.\n\nThe issue was traced to the `pack_ul_tti_request_pucch_pdu` and `unpack_ul_tti_request_pucch_pdu` functions missing the beamforming field handling. When these functions were called, the beamforming data was not being properly serialized/deserialized, causing data corruption.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Added beamforming structure packing/unpacking helper functions and updated PUCCH PDU processing to include beamforming data handling.\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Updated PRACH PDU processing to also handle beamforming data for consistency.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure a NR gNB with PUCCH beamforming enabled\n2. Send UL TTI requests with PUCCH PDUs containing beamforming configuration\n3. Observe that the beamforming parameters are not correctly processed\n4. Check that PUCCH transmission behavior does not match expected configuration\n\n"
}